4:
If it ain't Themis, in the flesh! Still got
them moves, huh?
6:
...You're from FQPress. I don't believe
you have permission to gather my
data.
8:
Aw, don't be like that. You know
we're the only outlet that didn't get
to write an article on the AI biz, right?
13:
Wait, you're not gonna chase me
away?
16:
If that's the only question you have,
then I'm leaving.
19:
Whoa, all right, all right. Just wanted
to dig into an interesting bit of info
that's been floating around the net.
It's about PBC.
20:
Heard that the whole AI thing was
staged by King Johnson to promote
the hero Nate. Is that true?
29:
FQPress? Bet they're loving all the
drama that's going around right
now.
32:
I looked into the social media posts
they were talking about, but every
source came from posters who
bought their followers.
36:
Ugh, why is the boss man so good at
predicting this kinda stuff and ONLY
this kinda stuff?
40:
Should I take that to mean King
Johnson is purposefully letting this
happen?
45:
Heck yeah he is. He lives for the
drama. Thinks it's great for publicity.
49:
Knowing him, that's not really
surprising... Though shouldn't he be
a little more concerned?
52:
The slander against you is
increasing by the minute.
55:
...Even though I'm the one who's
really at fault for everything.
59:
Now that's not true. If we want to
point fingers, then it's actually
Johnson's fault for spreading that
tech around in the first place.
64:
That's still no reason for you to take
any of the blame!
68:
...All these people see what they
want to, regardless of the truth. I
can't stand it.
71:
...Is that how it was when the first
Themis died?
75:
They called me the Executor of
Justice—a hero who carried on my
master's work to excise evil.
77:
But none of that was true. All I had in
my heart was revenge.
80:
You once said that Themis was a
hero who saved people... but that
was never who I was.
83:
I strongly believed that weakness
was the cause of evil, and evil drove
the weak to seek more evil.
86:
Therefore, weakness itself was evil. I
fought a lot with my master over
this belief.
93:
I looked up to my master for being
strong and upstanding. A true
benevolent hero.
96:
He always said that strength was a
gift, and that the strong had a
responsibility to share their abilities
with the weak.
99:
Both he and I categorized people as
either strong or weak, but you...
you're different.
102:
Your type of justice was convenient
back then... But how do you feel
about it now that it's resulted in this?
109:
Everyone's got their own morals, you
know? So in their own mind, they're
doing what's right.
113:
...That sounds suspiciously a lot like
"the ends justify the means."
117:
Okay, if we jump to the extreme
ends of things, sure! But I never said
anything about going that far!
119:
Besides, look at how things are
already. Even Noxel and AltMeme
operate with different goals in mind.
They do things that people riding
solo never could.
122:
We've all got different strengths,
goals, and support backing us up,
so it makes sense that we want
different things... No matter how
stupid it might seem to others.
125:
At the end of the day, people are
just fighting for the world they
envision. But being brave enough to
even try... is strength, if you ask me.
129: To fight for the world you envision...
133:
That's enough of that! You're just
gonna kill your self-confidence if
you keep overthinking things.
141:
Look, a selfie's all it took for the fans
to come swarming! True justice
comes from appreciating cuties!
149:
There's a whole bunch of fans who
love just seeing us doing well and
having a good time.
152:
They're the type to wish for world
peace so they can focus on the
good things in life. There's justice in
that sort of thinking, right?
155:
More than that... They believe in
someone like me, so who am I to
deny them their justice?
159:
...I can never win against you. But I
love you for it.
167: I'm not joking around. I mean it.
170:
You believe in others' potentials, no
matter who they are, and you draw
out the best from those you interact
with.
173:
...The shine within people that you so
admire is something that my
master and I would've never
perceived on our own.
176:
You broaden my horizons—make
my life better just by being at my
side.
180:
Wh-wha... You c-can't just say
things like that...
183:
You saw a shine in me that no one
else did... Freed it from the hatred
that was blinding my eyes.
192:
I-I... I've gotta... I need to go report to
my boss!
198:
So that's how that awkward selfie
got posted. Would explain why you
didn't bother posing.
201:
I'm not sure I would've known how to
pose there, even if I was given a
warning. Luckily, the fans ate it up.
204:
But enough about that. Have you
finished looking into FQPress?
206:
They're as shady as shady gets. I
don't think they're going to come
quietly.
209: What she said has merit, but...
212:
I know better than anyone that good
intentions can warp your actions. It's
even worse for people who have no
good in them.
215:
As a hero, it's my job to punish evil
and protect the people.
